o, Marche, Italy","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Llywelyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Llewellyn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Llewellyn","meanings":["Welsh: from the personal name <i>Llywelyn</i>, derived from British Celtic <i>Lugubelinos</i>, itself from the divine name <i>Lugus</i> + an uncertain second element often used alone as a name. Through association with <i>llew</i> ‘lion’, it was altered to <i>Llewelyn</i>. This was the name of two princes of north Wales who held the Normans at bay for many years in the 13th century. Etymologically speaking, the form with a fourth <i>-l-</i> is an error, not found as an original Welsh name, but this is now much the most common spelling in the US."]}]},{"name":"Efa","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of several Anglicized forms of the Gaelic name Eithne . In the case of Queen Victoria's granddaughter Princess Ena (Victoria Eugénie Julia Ena,  1887–1969 ) it had a different origin: it was a misreading by the minister who baptized her off a handwritten note of the originally intended name   Eva .  In England, the name is remembered principally as that of the fearsome  Ena Sharples  in the television soap opera Coronation Street.  See also  Ina ."],"variants":[{"name":"Eithne","meanings":["Traditional name, apparently from <i>eithne</i> ‘kernel’, which was used as a term of praise in bardic poetry. St Eithne was a daughter of King Laoghaire and one of St Patrick's first converts."]}]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Efa ferch Llywelyn was born about 1332, in Llandyfriog, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Llewelyn Fychan ap Llewelyn of Glamorgan, was 64 and her mother, Magerd verch Hywal, was 34. She married Ieuan Ap llywellen about 1360. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died after 1375, in Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"ABT    1332–Aft 1375":"umbes 1332–pärast 1375","1332–1375":"1332–1375","1302–Male":"1302–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1384–Male":"1384–Surnud","1348–Male":"1348–Surnud","1350–1447":"9.jaanuar1350kuni8.jaanuar1351–1447","1270–1338":"1270–1338","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","about 1360":"umbes 1360","ABT    1332":"umbes 1332","Aft 1375":"pärast 1375","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","1350":"9. jaanuar 1350 kuni 8. jaanuar 1351","1270":"1270","1338":"1338","1447":"1447","1348":"1348","after 1338":"pärast 1338","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1332":"1332","about 1348":"umbes 1348","1375":"1375","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","of Corrws,Llandyfriog,Cardiganshire,Wales":"Llandyfriog, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Llanuwchllyn, Merionethshire, Wales":"Llanuwchllyn, Merionethshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Breconshire, Wales":"Breconshire, Wales","{Cdfr ap Dnwl}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Itaalia"},"fi":{"ABT    1332–Aft 1375":"noin 1332–1375 jälkeen","1332–1375":"1332–1375","1302–Male":"1302–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1384–Male":"1384–Kuollut","1348–Male":"1348–Kuollut","1350–1447":"vuodesta9.tammikuuta1350vuoteen8.tammikuuta1351–1447","1270–1338":"1270–1338","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","about 1360":"noin 1360","ABT    1332":"noin 1332","Aft 1375":"1375 jälkeen","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","1350":"vuodesta 9. tammikuuta 1350 vuoteen 8. tammikuuta 1351","1270":"1270","1338":"1338","1447":"1447","1348":"1348","after 1338":"1338 jälkeen","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1332":"1332","about 1348":"noin 1348","1375":"1375","Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Corrw